[[!meta title="Numerous security holes in Tails 0.22.1"]]
[[!pagetemplate template="news.tmpl"]]

[[!tag security/fixed]]

Several security holes affect Tails 0.22.1.

We **strongly** encourage you to [[upgrade to Tails
0.23|news/version_0.23]] as soon as possible.

Details
=======

 - Iceweasel and its bundled NSS: [[!mfsa 2014-15]], [[!mfsa 2014-16]],
   [[!mfsa 2014-17]], [[!mfsa 2014-19]], [[!mfsa 2014-26]],
   [[!mfsa 2014-27]], [[!mfsa 2014-28]], [[!mfsa 2014-29]],
   [[!mfsa 2014-30]], [[!mfsa 2014-31]]
 - Linux kernel: [[!cve 2014-1438]], [[!cve 2013-4579]]
 - Iceweasel
 - cups: [[!debsa2014 2876]]
 - mutt: [[!debsa2014 2874]]
 - file: [[!debsa2014 2861]], [[!debsa2014 2873]]
 - udisks: [[!debsa2014 2872]]
 - libyaml-libyaml-perl: [[!debsa2014 2870]]
 - gnutls26: [[!debsa2014 2869]]
 - libtar: [[!debsa2014 2863]]
